.TH PAM_FACIAL_AUTH 8 "2025-01" "pam_facial_auth" "PAM Module"
.SH NAME
pam_facial_auth \- PAM module for facial recognition authentication

.SH SYNOPSIS
Add the following line to a PAM stack:

.PP
.B auth required pam_facial_auth.so
[options]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B pam_facial_auth
module performs facial recognition authentication using the LBPH model
trained using the provided tools.

It loads the userâ€™s model from
.BR /etc/pam_facial_auth/models .
The module uses OpenCV to open the webcam, detect a face, and match it
against the stored model.

This module is intended to be used as an additional authentication factor
after the standard PAM password check.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B config=/path/file
Configuration file (default:
/etc/security/pam_facial.conf).

.TP
.B device=/dev/videoX
Webcam device path.

.TP
.B threshold=value
LBPH confidence threshold (lower values = better match).

.TP
.B nogui=on|off
Disable GUI windows (default: on for PAM).

.TP
.B debug=on|off
Enable debug logging in syslog.

.TP
.B model=/path/dir
Custom model directory containing USER.xml.

.SH FILES
.TP
.B /etc/pam_facial_auth/
Base directory for images and models.

.TP
.B /etc/security/pam_facial.conf
Global configuration file.

.TP
.B /var/log/pam_facial_auth.log
Optional debug log if configured.

